gaby(){return"Definitions"},
gabx(){return"The terms used in this notice correspond to the definitions under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), in particular \u201cpersonal data\u201d, \u201cprocessing\u201d, and \u201ccontroller\u201d."},
gabM(){return"Purposes of processing and categories of data"},
gabJ(){return"We process personal data only to the extent necessary to provide a functional application and our content and services. This includes in particular:"},
gabL(){return"Server log data (e.g., IP address, date, time, requested resources, user agent) for providing and securing the service. The retention of operational/access logs depends on the plan; under the Supabase Free plan they are generally available only for a short time (approx. 24 hours)."},
gabK(){return"Registration and profile data (e.g., name, e-mail address, username; optional: choir/group affiliation) for managing user accounts and permissions."},
gabH(){return"Event data, song assignments, and attendance information for organizing choir rehearsals, church services, and other events."},
gabG(){return"Communication data that you send us via contact forms or support requests, for processing your enquiries."},
gabI(){return"No newsletters at present."},
gabF(){return"Legal bases"},
gabE(){return"We process personal data on the following legal bases: (1) Provision and use of the application, including management of user accounts \u2013 Article 6(1)(b) GDPR. (2) Technical provision, security, and error analysis (e.g., server/error logs) \u2013 Article 6(1)(f) GDPR; our legitimate interest lies in the secure and stable operation of the service. (3) Optional profile information (e.g., profile picture, date of birth, and other voluntary fields) insofar as not required for contract performance \u2013 based on your consent, Article 6(1)(a) GDPR; consent can be withdrawn at any time with effect for the future. (4) Where we are subject to legal obligations (e.g., commercial or tax retention duties in case of paid services), processing is based on Article 6(1)(c) GDPR."},
gabC(){return"Hosting and data processing on behalf"},
gabB(){return"The application is operated on servers of Supabase, Inc. (USA) (hosting/backend). Supabase processes personal data on our behalf; a data processing agreement pursuant to Article 28 GDPR has been concluded. Processing takes place in the region we selected on infrastructure provided by Amazon Web Services (e.g., EU/Frankfurt, eu-central-1). Where transfers to third countries are required (incl. the USA, Singapore), Supabase relies on the EU Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs). Contact: privacy@supabase.com."},
gabO(){return"Recipients of the data"},
gabN(){return"Personal data is only disclosed where necessary for performing our tasks or where you have given consent. Currently, there are no further recipients."},
gac0(){return"Storage period"},
gac_(){return"We store personal data only as long as necessary for the stated purposes or where statutory retention obligations apply. After the purpose ceases or statutory periods expire, the data is deleted or anonymised."},
gabX(){return"Your rights"},
gabS(){return"You have the following rights regarding the processing of your personal data:"},
